{
  "texts": [
    "We next investigate the theoretical basis of this generalizability advantage in the following proposition.",
    "Proposition 1 Let L be the objective loss function for training without adversarial perturbation, and assume that L is φ-Lipschitz and ψ-smooth.",
    "Then, the objective function of the CVaR-based training scheme in Eq. 5 is also φ-Lipschitz and max{φ, ψ}-smooth.",
    "1 shows that RT learning yields a smoother training process than AT, as it excludes the GE term (ϕ in Thm.",
    "1) associated with robust overfitting, resulting in a smaller overall GE."
  ]
}